                        "name": "aucahuasi",
                        "key": "aucahuasi",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=aucahuasi&avatarId=47450",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=aucahuasi&avatarId=47450",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=aucahuasi&avatarId=47450",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=aucahuasi&avatarId=47450"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Percy Camilo Trive\u00f1o Aucahuasi",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "I got this [^backtrace.log.cpp].\r\n\r\nIt seems we are moving the unique_locker and trying to lock some invalid mutex.\r\n\r\nAlso, I was able to get another issue, this time a deadlock using these values:\r\n{code:java}\r\nconstexpr int kNumIters = 1;\r\nconstexpr int kNumFragments = 10;\r\nconstexpr int kBatchesPerFragment = 10;\r\nconstexpr int kNumConcurrentTasks = 2;{code}\r\nI'll try to explore more about where we are getting these errors, so far I was able to reduce and reproduce the test issue using these values:\r\n{code:java}\r\nconstexpr int kNumIters = 1;\r\nconstexpr int kNumFragments = 2;\r\nconstexpr int kBatchesPerFragment = 1;\r\nconstexpr int kNumConcurrentTasks = 1;{code}\r\nGiven that we can use C++ 17 now, I'll try to use the new std::scoped_lock instead of the other lockers (in the places where it make sense to do so)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=aucahuasi",
                        "name": "aucahuasi",
                        "key": "aucahuasi",
                        "avatarUrls": {
